  "text": "The amount of bone available to place an implant is important although predictable strategies have been developed to enhance bone support through guided tissue regeneration and bone grafting. A number of classifications of bone characteristics have been developed but these are not used consistently. [CITATION_1] However, subjective assessment of bone quality is possible and implants placed in bone judged to be of good quality performed better than those placed in moderate or poor quality bone.",
